Package: conjointmatchups
Title: Reshape and Extract Matchups from Forced-Choice Conjoint Experiments
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alexander", "Coppock", email = "acoppock@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Matthew", "Blyth", role = "ctb"))
Description: Infrastructure for the data grammar of forced-choice (paired)
    conjoint experiments. Provides lossless reshaping between the profile-level
    (long, one row per candidate profile) and task-level (wide, one row per
    choice task) representations, and extraction of "matchups": the subset of
    tasks realizing a specified contrast between the two profiles, returned with
    a clean binary outcome ready for estimation. Complements single-experiment
    estimators such as 'cregg', 'cjoint', 'projoint', and 'factorEx' by
    producing the analysis-ready datasets they consume, and underlies the
    Average Feature Choice Probability (AFCP) estimand of Abramson, Kocak,
    Magazinnik, and Strezhnev.
